LUSIKISIKI President Jacob Zuma made an undertaking to the community of Lusikisiki and surrounding areas in the Eastern Cape, that all three spheres of government would intensify basic service delivery to the community, and ensure decisive action was taken to fight crime. President Zuma takes the podium to address the community of Lusikisiki on a number of issues including crime & service delivery #Siyahlola pic.twitter.com/5alzwTIzFcZuma paid a Siyahlola presidential monitoring visit to the area on Saturday, the presidency said in a statement.The president started his visit with a guided tour of the new Lusikisiki police station. We believe that this new police station will make a significant contribution to our fight to reduce crime in this community and defeat the scourge, particularly of gangsterism, in the form of Amavondo , about which I have received a number of complaints, he said. WATCH: President Zuma arrives at Lusikisiki Police Station as part of the #Siyahlola presidential monitoring visit pic.twitter.com/yYJlYyLrTy Community members then voiced their grievances to the president and also provided suggestions about how to fix them.They said government needed to address the root causes of crime and gangsterism, which were unemployment and the delivery of essential services to the community.Read: Service delivery struggles linked to post-apartheid failuresThey especially appealed for help to promote investment in factories and various industries in the area.The community also asked for the nearby R61 to be improved, the presidency said. #PoliceMinistry President Jacob Zuma & Police Minister @MbalulaFikile @ Lusikisiki to monitor government work, unveil new #SAPS Station. NP pic.twitter.com/m7wFiBtn8kThe ministers of police, justice, and social development, as well as the premier and provincial and local government leaders promised to attend to all the issues raised by the community, and directed residents to begin by accessing the mobile services that officials had brought to the community meetings.WATCH: AG releases findings of service delivery auditsZuma concluded the programme by undertaking to ensure that all the levels of government he brought to Lusikisiki worked speedily together to address all the challenges of the community. African News Agency